<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06059072 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06059072 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  An explosion in a remote section of a Colorado coal mine three milesunderground sent a fireball through a shaft to where miners were working,injuring 11 of them, officials said. Nine remained hospitalized today, fourwith serious injuries. Investigators worked through the night deep in theGolden Eagle coal mine near Weston to make sure gases that caused theexplosion early Wednesday were being vented properly.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  General News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  COAL MINE BLAST HURTS 11 COLORADO WORKERS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  National News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910228  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  February  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  71  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday February 28, 199100059072,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>